From ee70e13486c1e9dcaa00b87517afa37db8114374 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 20:21:43 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] TRUNK-6634: Run mysql-only changesets on MariaDB in 2.1.x
 update log

MariaDB 11 dropped the "5.5.5-" version-string prefix, so Liquibase now
detects it as MariaDB rather than MySQL and silently skips changesets
declared with dbms="mysql". In the 2.1.x update log this leaves
cohort_member without its cohort_member_id primary key and causes the
unique constraint on cohort_member.uuid to fail on populated tables,
because the uuid backfill never ran.

Checksum-safety was verified empirically against Liquibase 4.32.0 for
both v8 and latest checksum versions:

- editing the changeSet-level dbms attribute does NOT change checksums
- adding a dbms precondition does NOT change checksums
- adding a modifySql block DOES change checksums

Accordingly:

- 201609171146-2.1 / -2.2 / -2.3 are extended in place to
  dbms="mysql,mariadb" (checksums unchanged, verified byte-identical)
- 201610042145-2.1 is left untouched, since supporting MariaDB there
  would require a new modifySql block; a dedicated mariadb-only
  changeset TRUNK-6634-2026-07-03-1000 performs the equivalent uuid
  backfill using valueComputed="UUID()" and is ordered before the
  unique-constraint changeset 201610042145-2.2

MariaDbUpdateChangeSetsTest pins the historical v8 checksums recorded
in the DATABASECHANGELOG of existing deployments so future edits that
would break checksum validation fail in CI, and asserts the mariadb
backfill ordering.

This commit was authored by Claude (Anthropic AI assistant); see the
pull request description for disclosure and verification details.
---
 .../liquibase-update-to-latest-2.1.x.xml      |  22 +++-
 .../MariaDbUpdateChangeSetsTest.java          | 122 ++++++++++++++++++
 2 files changed, 141 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)
 create mode 100644 api/src/test/java/org/openmrs/liquibase/MariaDbUpdateChangeSetsTest.java

diff --git a/api/src/main/resources/org/openmrs/liquibase/updates/liquibase-update-to-latest-2.1.x.xml b/api/src/main/resources/org/openmrs/liquibase/updates/liquibase-update-to-latest-2.1.x.xml
index 784f753..da4bdbb 100644
--- a/api/src/main/resources/org/openmrs/liquibase/updates/liquibase-update-to-latest-2.1.x.xml
+++ b/api/src/main/resources/org/openmrs/liquibase/updates/liquibase-update-to-latest-2.1.x.xml
@@ -74,7 +74,7 @@
 			</column>
 		</addColumn>
 	</changeSet>
-	<changeSet author="vshankar" id="201609171146-2.1" dbms="mysql">
+	<changeSet author="vshankar" id="201609171146-2.1" dbms="mysql,mariadb">
 		<preConditions onFail="MARK_RAN">
 			<and>
 				<columnExists tableName="cohort_member" columnName="cohort_member_id"/>
@@ -88,14 +88,14 @@
 		<comment>Updating cohort member ids</comment>
 		<customChange class="org.openmrs.util.databasechange.UpdateCohortMemberIdsChangeset"/>
 	</changeSet>
-	<changeSet author="vshankar" id="201609171146-2.2" dbms="mysql">
+	<changeSet author="vshankar" id="201609171146-2.2" dbms="mysql,mariadb">
 		<preConditions onFail="MARK_RAN">
 			<columnExists tableName="cohort_member" columnName="cohort_member_id"/>
 		</preConditions>
 		<comment>Adding primary key to cohort_member.cohort_member_id</comment>
 		<addPrimaryKey tableName="cohort_member" columnNames="cohort_member_id"/>
 	</changeSet>
-	<changeSet author="vshankar" id="201609171146-2.3" dbms="mysql">
+	<changeSet author="vshankar" id="201609171146-2.3" dbms="mysql,mariadb">
 		<preConditions onFail="MARK_RAN">
 			<columnExists tableName="cohort_member" columnName="cohort_member_id"/>
 		</preConditions>
@@ -276,6 +276,22 @@
 		<modifySql dbms="mysql"><replace replace="name-of-uuid-function" with="UUID()"/></modifySql>
 		<modifySql dbms="oracle"><replace replace="name-of-uuid-function" with="SYS_GUID()"/></modifySql>
 	</changeSet>
+	<changeSet id="TRUNK-6634-2026-07-03-1000" author="claude" dbms="mariadb">
+		<preConditions onFail="MARK_RAN">
+			<columnExists tableName="cohort_member" columnName="uuid"/>
+		</preConditions>
+		<comment>
+			Generating UUIDs for rows in cohort_member on MariaDB. Changeset 201610042145-2.1 only
+			runs for MySQL and Oracle; since MariaDB 11 is no longer detected as MySQL, the uuid
+			backfill was silently skipped and the unique constraint in 201610042145-2.2 then failed
+			on tables with more than one row. 201610042145-2.1 must stay untouched because adding a
+			modifySql block changes its checksum and would break validation on existing databases.
+		</comment>
+		<update tableName="cohort_member">
+			<column name="uuid" valueComputed="UUID()"/>
+			<where>uuid = '' OR uuid is null</where>
+		</update>
+	</changeSet>
 	<changeSet id="201610042145-2.2" author="vshankar">
 		<preConditions>
 			<columnExists tableName="cohort_member" columnName="uuid"/>
diff --git a/api/src/test/java/org/openmrs/liquibase/MariaDbUpdateChangeSetsTest.java b/api/src/test/java/org/openmrs/liquibase/MariaDbUpdateChangeSetsTest.java
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..7628415
--- /dev/null
+++ b/api/src/test/java/org/openmrs/liquibase/MariaDbUpdateChangeSetsTest.java
@@ -0,0 +1,122 @@
